        <div id="container">
            <main class=""><article class="main-content"><h1 class="">Roughriders News</h1>
        <p class="">We love to share the accomplishments of our students and staff! Visit this page often to catch up on the latest details about recent events, upcoming activities, and more. You can even read the latest edition of the Western Front newsletter. We encourage you to bookmark this page, as we’ll update it often!</p>
            <div class="newsItem">
<a name="AmendedSchoolClosureAndStayAtHomeOrders"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Amended School Closure and Stay-at-Home Orders</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">Please take a few minutes to review these important orders:</p>
<div class="pom-container"><ul class="">
<li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/March-30-2020-Ammended-Order-On-Closure-for-All-K-12-Schools.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">March 30, 2020: Amended Order - Closure of All K–12 Ohio Schools</a></li>
<li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/March-30-2020-Board-Resolution-Stay-at-Home-Order-Ratification-Certified.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">March 30, 2020: Board Resolution - Stay-at-Home Order Ratification</a></li>
<li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/April-2-2020-Amended-Directors-Stay-at-Home-Order.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">April 2, 2020: Amended Director's Stay-at-Home Order</a></li>
<li class=""><a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/April-3-2020-One-Call-Message-COVID-19.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">April 3, 2020: One Call Now Message</a></li>
</ul></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="schoolbuildingsandofficesclosed"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">School Buildings and Offices Closed</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">For everyone's protection, school buildings and offices are closed until further notice. However, we are standing by to answer your questions and address your concerns via email:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Elementary Principal Jennifer Cornelison at <a href="mailto:jcornelison@western-reserve.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">jcornelison@western-reserve.org</a>
</li>
<li class="">Middle/High School Principal Lisa Border at <a href="mailto:lborder@western-reserve.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">lborder@western-reserve.org</a>
</li>
<li class="">Special Education Supervisor Lisa Muenz at <a href="mailto:lmuenz@western-reserve.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">lmuenz@western-reserve.org</a>
</li>
<li class="">Athletics Director Ryan Falknor at <a href="mailto:rfalknor@western-reserve.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">rfalknor@western-reserve.org</a>
</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p class="">For individual teachers' email addresses, please visit our <a href="/Administration-and-Staff" title="" alt="" target="_self">Administration and Staff page</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="everydayheroes"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Everyday Heroes</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class=""><img src="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Graphics/photonews_everydayheroes_041420.png" alt="Food staff members pose together with food in a kitchen" class="float-right" style="max-width: 300px; width: 100%;">A month ago, when students and teachers went home, members of our food-service, transportation, and custodial departments simply would not stand down. They knew that without them the students may not be able to eat and have the necessary supplies to complete the assignments teachers were creating for them. Their time, selflessness, and caring spirit are what make the WR community like no other. Each day they prepare and deliver over 1,000 meals to students in the community. We deliver 500 breakfasts and 500 lunches to homes each morning.</p>
<p class="">The district’s plan is to continue to provide this service to students throughout the duration of our mandated leave. Should we have an interruption from our food distribution services that would delay deliveries temporarily, we will communicate with families immediately. We appreciate the continued displays of support to these departments as they travel their route each day. Your signs, sidewalk chalk, and WR spirit make their effort worthwhile. We are in this together WR, and some incredible everyday heroes lead us.</p>
<div class="pom-container clearfix"></div>
<p></p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="thankyouwrstaff"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Thank You WR Staff</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">Using the recommended social distancing standards, the WR staff was able to successfully and safely return belongings to students on April 8. Please continue to maintain contact with teachers about your students’ studies, or reach out to administration if you have any questions.</p>
<div class="pom-container"><img src="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Graphics/photonews_thankyouwrstaff_041420.png" alt="Staff members standing outside of the school with their arms spread out to display distance" class="" style="max-width: 450px; width: 100%;"></div>
<p></p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="kindergartenregistration"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">2020–2021 Kindergarten Registration</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">Western Reserve Elementary School is accepting registration for the 2020–2021 kindergarten class. Students must be five years old by August 1 to enroll. The enrollment packet is available on our <a href="/Registration" title="" alt="" target="_self">Registration page</a>, and you can <a href="mailto:athomas@western-reserve.org" title="" alt="" target="_top">email it to Autumn Thomas</a> for processing. You can also call the school's main line at (419) 660-9824 and leave a message on extension 1004, and we will email the enrollment papers to you.</p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="electronicdeviceloanprogram"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Electronic Device Loan Program</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">In order to meet the academic needs of our students, the district has implemented a Google Chromebook loan program. Parents who have an interest in borrowing a device can fill out a survey indicating their agreement to follow the district acceptable use policy.</p>
<p class="">If you have an interest in borrowing a Google Chromebook in order to facilitate online learning for your student at Western Reserve (WR), please complete the survey below. Please note that we will only distribute one device per household. If you have more than one WR student in your household, please encourage your children to share the device for their instructional activities/assignments. Please <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/Electronic-Device-Loan-Program.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">see our electronic device loan program flyer</a> for more information.</p>
<p class=""></p>
<ul><li class=""><a href="https://forms.gle/PiaEYo373F4AeUNt8" title="" alt="" target="_blank" class="">Electronic Device Request Survey</a></li></ul>
<p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="triptowashingtondc"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">8th Grade Trip to Washington, D.C. </div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class=""><p class="">The 8th grade trip to Washington, D.C. has been postponed until September 2020. Please <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/Washington-DC-Itinerary.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">see the revised itinerary</a> for more information. Athletes, <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/Athletics-Schedule-September-2020.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">please review the September 2020 athletics schedule</a> and talk to your coaches in advance.</p></div></div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="covid19pressrelease"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">Local Superintendents Announce Protocols Regarding Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19)</div>
	<div class="newsbody">
<p class="">School officials from area public schools conducted a meeting today to announce a series of common protocols for addressing novel coronavirus (COVID-19). While there are no reported cases of the COVID-19 in our immediate area, multiple area superintendents met to provide a collaborative response to the current health challenge in our state and nation.</p>
<p class="">There was agreement on the following matters:</p>
<ul>
<li class="">Any possible closing of schools would be announced jointly and be made in consultation with a county or state health official;</li>
<li class="">Providing electronic options to students to address academic work in the event of the closure of school for multiple days;</li>
<li class="">Agreement to suspend all large gatherings for thirty days (until April 10) and then reassess the next steps at that time;</li>
<li class="">Districts will provide deep cleaning of buildings and facilities;</li>
<li class="">Agreement to partner with the County Health Department and officials regarding strategic steps and recommendations for specific action; and</li>
<li class="">Districts will develop regular communication protocols to maintain communications with students, parents, and community members.</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p class="">Huron County Public Health’s (HCPH) Health Commissioner, Timothy Hollinger, provided his support of the above listed community containment measures and is committed to continuing to work with Huron County School Districts to protect the health of Huron County residents.</p>
<p class="">Each school district will be conducting communications to their constituents on this matter. The purpose of this press release is to provide a consistent set of protocols for schools within the immediate area. Follow up questions regarding local school actions can be directed to each of the Superintendents. General information about COVID-19 can be found at the <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html" title="" alt="" target="_blank" class="">Center for Disease Control and Prevention's website</a>. If residents have further general questions about COVID-19 they should call 1-833-4ASKODH. If residents have specific health-related questions, they should contact their physician. </p>
<p class="">For more information, <a href="https://tb2cdn.schoolwebmasters.com/accnt_447764/site_447765/Documents/Coronavirus-Press-Release.pdf" title="" alt="" target="_blank">please review our press release in its entirety</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="newsItem">
<a name="_March122020OneCall"></a>
	<div class="newstitle">COVID-19 Update: March 12, 2020</div>
	<div class="newsbody"><div class="">
<p class="">We sent the following message on March 12, 2020</p>
<p class="">You may have heard that Governor Dewine has closed Ohio public and private schools for roughly three weeks. At this time, we do not have the governor’s official executive order, which will determine which of the three plans we will execute. </p>
<p class="">Yes, please know that the district has various plans in place which even include delivery of lessons and meals to those in need. Schooling will continue during this time. We will post the details of our plan on our website and Facebook page, but not until we have the official orders from the governor. We will call when the plan specifics are ready for viewing. </p>
<p class="">Please continue to visit our website and Facebook pages in the days to come and expect additional information over the course of the next week. You may direct follow-up questions regarding specific school actions to the superintendent’s office or to each of the school principals. Thank you.</p>
</div></div>
